equipment_data.description: An inexpensive blade, available wherever swords are sold. When a swordsman in training takes that all-important first swing, they're usually holding one of these.
A dagger designed to look like a pen. It may not be mightier than the sword, but it's a lot easier to conceal.
A wooden weapon made to protect the fists. The design, though simple, does reduce some of the impact on the joints.
A stock-standard wooden bow, favored by hunters. With its excellent power and range, it's perfect for bagging all kinds of game.
A spear often wielded by soldiers. Its ease of use and long reach make it a popular choice on the battlefield.
A small axe held in one hand. Originally made for throwing, it has proven so easy to wield that it is often used in melee combat.
A staff made from the wood of the Astraean cypress, a fragrant tree that grows in the Mysterion Woods. Its scent helps calm the wounded.
Originally an apron for craftsmen, as evidenced by the large front pocket. Fledgling adventurers use this extra storage space to carry lots of gear.
A favored first choice of adventurers. The name is meant to instill luck to all those making that first foray into the world.
A shield made from a coniferous tree known as the Astraean Cedar. Cheap and easily made, they are a common sight among warriors-in-training.
A standard item that is loved by not only adventurers. Light and easy to walk in. The longer you wear them the more comfortable they become.
Originally a hat worn by painters. Because it's handy against the sun and wind, it's a popular item for novice adventurers.
A mysterious bracelet that energizes the wearer. Increases attack.
An amulet featuring a four-leaf clover. It is said that it brings good luck and protection to the person who wears it.
A bracelet with magical power. When worn, it raises your spirits and increases magic attack.
An unusual sword with a blade and handle connected by gears. A weapon created by a watchmaker and a blacksmith.
A replica of a great sword presented to a certain noble. Not only is it beautiful, it is sharp and practical.
A beautiful sword that glows in the colors of the northern lights. The blade emits light every time it is wielded, and in its wake the light appears to dance.
A beautifully curved sword. It's such a fine blade that a brave and well-known general once said that it would be a shame for it to be sullied by blood.
A knife that is more useful in the forest or mountains rather than in battle. Various gimmicks for survival are packed within it.
Leather gloves embedded with metal that make punches hit harder. Designed for martial artists who strive to make their body a true weapon.
A bow made using materials gathered from the Crystal Mountains. The crystals act as a magical catalyst, enabling it to fire enchanted arrows.
A polearm named after the weapon of the sea-god Poseidon, which held the power to sink continents beneath the waves.
A spear imbued with the strength of a fire spirit. The more monsters it slays, the more fiercely its flame-shaped head blazes.
A steel battle axe. Unlike its cousins made for chopping wood, this axe was intended to be a weapon and is thus quite lethal.
A battle axe crafted using advanced metalworking techniques. Decimates foes with attacks that make full use of its weight.
A rod made by elves, a folk with strong ties to nature. Used both as a weapon and as an implement in prayers for plentifulness.
A cane topped by a dragon clutching an orb. Imbued with faint traces of draconic might.
A staff that facilitates the casting of recovery spells. A favorite of magical healers.
A staff made with the precious horn of a unicorn. The horn has restorative powers and enhances healing magic.
Robes once worn by a priest traveling the continent to spread his faith. Beloved by spellcasters for being hardy while allowing ease of movement.
Armor made from thin plates. Light and nimble, it's characterized by reliable defense and ease of movement.
Armor made of leather and metal arranged like scales. Easy to move around in and strong against slashes or thrusts, but weak against blows from blunt weapons.
Solid armor made with advanced casting techniques. The wearer becomes immune to ordinary attacks.
Clothes that have been woven with a legendary Astraean pattern. You need the proper status and pedigree to purchase it.
There is no better attire for working in the dark. It is said that in some countries, professional spies use it habitually.
A lovely robe reminiscent of spring. The robe is very durable and suitable for travel. Its design and practicality make it a favorite among many people.
A favorite item in the cold, northern countries. The warm yarn is spun from sheep's wool, and the cape weaved from it protects the shoulders and arms from the severe climate.
A metal shield as big as a person's body. It provides overwhelming protection, but is difficult to move with because of its weight.
These stylish boots are inspired by a clown. When you wear them, you will feel happy and cheerful.
Boots made with the bones of monsters that inhabit the high mountains. Its wild design will awaken the wild heart within!
Footwear worn by magic-users during travels to collect potion ingredients. Built sturdily enough to withstand even the harshest of environments.
A casquette with goggles attached. It has a cute, balloon-like silhouette and is all the rage with Landosol's teens.
A helmet used by ancient warriors. It is so sturdy that it can still be used in the modern age.
A hood used by nuns. They say that these nuns have healed not only the bodies, but also the spirits, of injured people.
An orb that grants valor, one of the three key attributes of a warrior. Provides the courage to face any foe in battle without fear.
A strength-enhancing bracelet adorned with the spiked scales of a monster. The viciousness of that beast makes it a rarity out on the market.
An orb that grants virtue, one of the three key attributes of a warrior. Instills a compassionate heart that strives to protect oneself and others.
A bracelet for knights woven with prayers of a safe return home. These wishes keep the wearer safe by boosting defensive abilities.
Special glasses made from ensorceled stone that heighten the wearer's magic attack power.
An orb that grants wisdom, one of the three key attributes of a warrior. Improves spellcasting by clearing the mind and granting intelligence.
A monocle used by a noble wizard. Runes are engraved on the metal frame, raising the magic power of the wearer.
A silver bracelet decorated with magic stones and special engravings. It revitalizes the flow of magic and increases the magic power of the wearer.
A curved blade made of meteorite shards. The blade shines like stardust when bathed in light.
A sword emblazoned with the fiery breath of a dragon. Its wide blade is better for slashing than thrusting, and its wielder will look like a dragon beautifully in motion.
A wizard used this blade specifically for close combat. Since he was physically weak, he enchanted the feathers of a large bird and used them to create this extremely light sword.
A sword granted to those licensed in a sword style taught in an eastern kingdom. It contains moonlight and heightens the wielder's five senses along with their sixth sense.
It is said that a powerful samurai defeated a thunder beast with this sword. This sword is imbued with the power of lightning.
A dagger made from very expensive platinum. Many aristocrats keep one at their side for self-defense.
A fearsome dagger with its own will and a constant thirst for blood. When bathed in blood, rather than rusting, it shines even more bewitchingly.
A claw in the shape of the jaws of a vicious black dragon. It enables the wearer to see in the dark. An assassin who once used this claw soaked it in poison to increase its lethality.
A man once gifted his sweetheart the game he took down with this bow. In tribute, he named the bow after the god of love.
A bow made by demons persecuted by people and driven deep underground. They have defeated many humans entering their territory with this bow.
A halberd given to a prestigious knight. Its unbreakable blade represents the pride of a knight fighting for his country and people.
A spear that can kill with a single blow. Its deadly power easily penetrates even the strongest armor, stopping the enemy's breath with a single thrust.
A battle axe with a blue, astronomical object. The astronomical object symbolizes the world itself and absorbs the energy of the earth to imbue the wearer with power.
Every time this axe decorated with brilliant flowers is wielded, a large, new ring of fresh blood blooms.
An axe made in a workshop specializing in advanced weapon manufacturing. It is possible to store lightning inside the axe and release it when attacking.
A staff used by a group of brutal wizards. This staff has been dyed red with the blood of its victims.
A wizard is said to have obtained this item through a deal with a devil. The souls of its victims are believed to be offered to the devil.
A staff used by a clan of wizards who are astrologers by trade. They observe the stars and predict the future.
The desire to save others causes these buds to bloom. Their untainted energy is the source of their healing power.
Armor made with a strong and fashionable knight in mind. However, no matter how fashionable one may be, without actual strength, one's charm will be severely reduced.

The armor of a female warrior who defeated a series of strong men and became queen of the arena. It is said that one look into her beastly eyes will cause her opponents in the battlefield to lose their will to fight.
Armor made of thick steel plates. Forgoing lightness, it specializes in defense, and is favored by warriors who use axes and swords.
A knight with a penchant for flamboyance had this armor made for him. His bravado caused him to stand out on the battlefield, attracting enemies to his location.
A piece of clothing consisting of a leather robe over fabric. It provides excellent protection against the cold and is suitable for gathering materials in cold weather.
A noble dress for a female knight of the royal castle. The dress is made of fine leather and black gold, and the chest adorned with a symbol indicating the status of a knight.
The clothes worn by the Elven Queen during peace treaty meetings with other races. Elvenfolk endowed it with a powerful magic veil just in case.
This robe is modeled on a garment worn by the god of love. With feathers that float magically on its back, the robe is often mistaken for the real thing.
The robes of a philosopher who supported a child emperor. He taught the boy the right path and principles, leading the country to a better future.
The shield of a brave and courageous general. From the battle's front line, he personally cut into the enemy's territory and led the army to victory.
Special boots that make footsteps silent. Rumors say Eastern spies wore such boots, but they remain a mystery.
Boots made for swordsmen who use rapiers and other slender swords. They are very light, perfect for those who seek mobility over strength.
A mage's formal boots. They are enchanted so they never get dirty, no matter where they go.
A helmet used by knights who worship the now deceased black dragon. They continued to take the lives of innocent people as sacrifices for the dragon.
A headband that a wizard's family gives to a daughter leaving the home for training. The mother kneads in her own magical power, creating it with love.
A traditional mage's hat adorned with accessories that impove their magic.
Magical opal earrings. The wearer's body will overflow with vitality and attack power will increase.
A headdress made from feathers of a Gryphon, a creature with the head and wings of an eagle and the body of a lion. The power of a ferocious beast dwells within it.
A rare scarlet diamond. It is said to contain the flames of a dragon. By equipping it, one will gain power like that of a raging fire.
Magical emerald earrings. The wearer gains an indomitable spirit and increased defense.
An eight-pointed star that represents infinite circulation. It absorbs eight naturally occurring elements to endow the wearer with continuous protection.
Once owned by a king known as Lionheart. Having spent most of his life in battle, many people revered him for his bravery.
Magical turquoise earrings. The wearer gains wisdom and increased magical attack power.
Magical pearl earrings. The wearer gains better mental concentration and magical power.
Wise men use this in Grotto Quests for energy flows. The energy flowing through the ground is studied and used to investigate the conditions of the environment and continent.
It is said that after the spirit Daphne transformed herself into a laurel tree, Apollo, who loved her, wore a leaf from her tree as a sign of his eternal love.
Once wielded by a powerful archangel, this brilliant silver blade contains the power that banishes all evil with a single swing.
A sword said to be blessed by the sun god Apollo. The person who wielded this sword was called the Sun King. He made history and brought prosperity to the realm for many years.
A magical sword that activates ice magic as it strikes its wielder's enemies. Because it uses ice fairy magic, the sword is always cold to the touch.
A demon blade that has consumed the blood of many thousands of victims. Cursed to turn its wielder into a slave to its thirst for blood, but if you can control it, its strength is second to none.
A sword that sleeps deep in the ruins of the forest. The person chosen by this sword can reach its location upon being invited by a butterfly.
A sword of light crafted over a lifetime by a swordsmith who received a vision from the Goddess of Light, Aglaia. The sword was in the possession of a brave man who used it to oppose the Demon God.
A noble falcon sword that rules the sky. Swinging this sword is like a falcon aiming for its prey; its magic-infused edge accurately strikes the enemy's vital points.
A blade imbued with the powers of a divine bird said to appear at the rising of the sun. Wreathed in flames that reflect the wielder's strength of will, in the right hands it can even melt steel.
A dagger said to have been given to the king of the humans by a dwarf master craftsman. The material used to make it is unknown and unlike any existing ore.
A royal heirloom dagger in the oldest kingdom in history. The sword was handed down to princesses over generations, bestowing them with magic to protect their country.
A dagger made to purge wicked wizards tainted by evil magic who have lost their humanity. It prevents the activation of magic.
A knife that can only be wielded by the purest of maidens. As it repels all sin and corruption, those with hearts tainted by evil cannot even touch it.
A crimson gauntlet forged in the flames of purgatory. The flames emanating from the gauntlet burn enemies into oblivion.
A golden gauntlet used by a famous king called Lionheart. It is said that the gauntlet gives its wearer unlimited power and the promise of becoming a fierce warrior.
A claw containing the magic of the Ice Goddess, who single-handedly destroyed an entire army. Its cutting wind freezes foes like a blizzard, crushing the enemy's will to fight.
A gauntlet blessed by a terrible lightning deity. With each blow, it sends blue sparks flying that sear the flesh of its foes and can even cause storm clouds to gather.
A hero imbued the power of lightning into his bow to slay a man-eating sea dragon. The arrows infused with the power of lightning are said to have felled the sea dragon in a single blow.
A great bow used by an Archangel in the apocalyptic war against the devil in a bygone era. It is said that the force of the arrows from this bow reached Cocytus, the Ninth Circle of Hell.
A bow blessed by the Goddess of Hunting. Its arrows drive away evil, never miss their targets, and can turn the tide of battle with a single shot.
A bow carved from the wood of an ancient spiritual tree. Filled with the energies of the spirit world, each arrow it fires is sure to find its mark.
A spear that was thrust into the back of a dragon living in a volcano. Since the tip of the spear was in the body of the dragon for many years, it now bears the power of fire.
A large spear used by a legendary queen who ruled the entire continent. She was both wise and adept at fighting, using this spear to seize the continent.
A famous spear that belonged to a legendary knight. A single thrust of this spear creates a whirlwind that sweeps away all surrounding enemies.
A polearm blessed by the mother goddess of the land. As unyielding as the earth, it grants its wielder fortitude and strength beyond compare.
Evil dragons that threatened the world of mankind were sealed in this axe by heroes of every region. The axe, in which the spirits of the dragons reside, emits evil energy.
A double-edged axe that contains hellfire. Its body is red like blood; a single swing will douse the enemy in crimson flames, burning them down to their bones.

The queen's axe that helped her stand tall on the frontlines of battle. While it is unbelievably heavy, its recognized owner is able to wield it easily. Its blade can smash through the most robust gates of a city with a single blow.
An axe brimming with the blessings of water spirits. Though it weighs little, its blade is sharp enough to carve through precious minerals with the slightest effort.
The staff belonged to a wizard who became a vengeful demon after his wife was murdered. He caged his own anger in this staff and killed everyone involved in his wife's murder.
A mysterious staff that is said to have been made by ancient sages using sun shards. It is said that whoever this staff chooses will be granted omniscience and omnipotence.
A ringed staff said to have been carried by the god of truth, justice, and peace. It is said those who hold the staff receive a divine vision.
A wand containing the soul of a high-ranking demon. Its full merciless potential is unleashed when casting spells to devastate the lives of those who stand against it.

This staff is said to have been used by the goddess of the moon to cure the illnesses of her faithful followers. Fearing her power, the god of death is said to have hidden the wand in the netherworlds.
A miracle staff made of giant branches from the Tree of Life. It is said that if you shake it, fresh, green leaves will sprout on a dead tree and water will spring forth from the ground.
A sacred staff imbued with the blessings of the phoenix. It grants an inexhaustible supply of magical energy.
A magical rod blessed by a benevolent messenger of the heavens. Its power resonates with the user's inner compassion, so spells that aid one's comrades become especially potent.
Enchanted armor that makes one invisible. A princess of a certain country once fell in love with someone she couldn't be with, so she used this armor to run away.
Supreme armor featuring a rare metal that has the brilliance of silver with a strength that surpasses steel, as well as beauty and toughness born from a master craftsman.
The armor of the proud and brave, who in the name of the gods defeated the heretics. The blessings of divine protection are only given to those with a pure soul.

The vivid red armor of a knightly princess who fought to defend her nation from a dark empress.\nIts wondrous glow struck fear into the hearts of her enemies, but filled her subjects' hearts with courage.
Armor used by angels in battle. Lower-level demons cannot even approach this armor as the light reflecting from its silver alone is enough to disintegrate them.
Armor imbued with the soul of a berserker who devoted himself to battle. Whoever wears this armor gains the power of a war demon.
The beautiful armor worn by a general, who many feared as the "grim reaper" of the battlefield. Enemy soldiers' morale would collapse at the sight of this violet-colored armor.
Heavy armor once worn by a legendary dragonslayer. Engraved with a dragon emblem, it is said to have withstood the beast's steel-tearing claws and infernal breath.
A priest, ordered by the king in secret, risked his life to create this beautiful vestment. Since the garment was sewn in the light of the moon, it glows in seven different colors when in moonlight.
The clothes of a hermit who peeked into the magic abyss. It was sewn with threads enchanted with magic power.
The robe of a pious mage willing to fight against even the gods for the sake of his people. The heavenly blessings imbued in these robes grant the wearer a will of steel.
The dress of an empress of darkness. Its pitch-black emblem, eerie as the creeping darkness itself, is said to have bewitched all of the world's evils and struck fear into the hearts of men.
A robe worn by a great mage who devoted his entire lifetime to magic. Due to this mage's mighty power, these robes still emit mysterious energies.
Robes worn by saints who confronted demons alongside angels. Their gallantry in battle became the stuff of legends.
The robe worn by a great sage who lived in a divine forest. Filled with the power of divine spirits, it protects the wearer from all kinds of evil forces.
A shield given only to the Queen's guards, in whom she places her absolute trust. It holds the power of absolute protection, even reflecting magic and curses.
The shield of a knight who devoted his life to protecting the princess in a small, turbulent country. Later, the princess became a queen and praised the knight as a hero.
Armor blessed with holy power, used by paladins who risk their lives to protect the people from monsters.
The sacred boots of a mythical creature. It allows the wearer to walk cooly through flames and ward off all attacks.
Armored footwear infused with the blessings of the fairy folk of old. In addition to their spiritual power, they are covered in mithril ornaments to amplify their purifying effects.
A special pair of boots given only to wizards recognized by the crown. Only an elder elf artisan can make such an item.
The favorite shoes of a necromancer many fear as the ruler of the underworld. It is said that anyone who hears the sound of these shoes is deprived of their energy and becomes enslaved to the wearer.
A beautiful pair of boots, blessed with the power of the great spirit of water. This superior spiritual energy serves as a catalyst to draw out the wearer's latent magical strength.
A helmet used by a demigod knight called the Sky Dancer. It is said that he would dance freely in the sky and toss his enemies in the air.
Proof one has attained the highest level of magic recognized by the state.\nThose who possess this hood\nare allowed to stand beside the king.
A hood worn by successive religious leaders during diplomatic affairs. It grants the wearer powers of exorcism and the ability to see through illusions.
A venerable crown worn by the queen of a magical kingdom. Using the crown's power to enhance her own magical abilities, she long brought order to her kingdom.
This special ore combines and encapsulates the magic of the four great spirits. It is the greatest creation of an extraordinary alchemist.
A necklace that uses jewels blessed by the sun god, specially crafted for those who resist demons. It allows one to face powerful enemies without fear.
A ring adorned with a ruby said to hold a flame that has burned since the beginning of time. The wearer can enshroud themselves in an all-consuming inferno.
A jeweled pendant said to have been created by a cat god. Blessed with superhuman vision and reflexes, the wearer will corner their prey without fail.
A legendary magic tool created by a long reigning emperor. It is said to help its wearer by bearing whatever misfortunes fall upon them.
This bracelet is decorated with crystals that contain the magic of the moon. The ethereal light emanating from the moon will cast blessings and shake off any curse.
A pendant granted only to those who have been chosen by a sacred spirit. The spirit's boundless love confers a powerful protection from all dangers.
An amulet of the moon goddess, whose loved one was harmed by an arrow. The magic of the waning moon repels flying arrows.
A rare ore formed from a dragon's tears that crystallized over an eternity. It makes its wearer's soul tremble as it houses the dragon's power.
A crystal ball into which a great sage poured all of his magical energies after leading an army to countless victories. Grants the holder wisdom to seize glory and success.
A greatsword born from the bolts of lightning hurled at the ground by a wrathful deity. Each swing sends sparks leaping across the sky above as it effortlessly carves through its foes.
A holy sword which acts as the key to open the gates to a sacred realm. Its divine aura banishes evil before the blade even so much as touches its target.
A two-handed sword said to slice not through living beings, but through the sins they bear. Those struck by this weapon suffer no wounds, but devote the rest of their lives to atonement.
A divine sword found enshrined in a sea god's temple, down in the ocean depths. Its watery blade can take any form the wielder wishes, even summoning floods, mist and whirlpools to torment their foe.
A sword that houses the power of a legendary lightwyrm. Because it is too sharp to safely hold, its power is controlled by golden engravings.

A crystalline blade bestowed by Mother Nature upon a righteous warlord. If thrust into the ground, sharp pillars of crystal erupt from the earth all the way to the world's end, driving back enemy hordes.
A greatsword blessed by the divine rabbit spirit of the earth. Though adorable in appearance, it deals strikes as rapid and plentiful as a whole herd of rabbits, quickly overwhelming the enemy.
A blade that shines with all the grace of pale cherry blossoms in full bloom. When the bell on its hilt rings out, enemies will meet with the same swift fate as the falling blossoms.
A magical sword from an empire that was tragically submerged.\nThe blade is inscribed with its homeland's history. Blessed by water spirits, it sweeps through the air like waves across the ocean.
A cursed katana that thirsts for human blood. If it judges its wielder unworthy, it will consume their life force, adding their soul's laments to the blight that it carries.

This crimson blade was forged from the very flames of a fire deity. Its scorching blade cleaves any material like a hot knife through butter, and it can summon infernos to reduce entire armies to ash.
This longsword is said to have been wielded by the God of Wind. The countless gales enveloping the blade will cut approaching enemies to pieces without touching them.
A ceremonial sword formerly used to invoke deities at religious festivals. The light of the gods still resides in the blade, and with a single swing it purges all evil.
A blade once wielded by a holy maiden who calmed a rampaging water deity. Its blade gleams like the divine carp that swims across the heavens, and each swing is as captivating as a sacred dance.
A dagger said to be blessed by a fertility deity. Its gleaming blade absorbs the vital energy of the natural world and channels it into each vivid strike.
A dagger inhabited by spirits of fire. Its blade, which reaches temperatures comparable to lava from a volcanic eruption, can melt its unlucky targets with a single touch.
A royal dagger passed down through generations of fairy monarchs. The arcane runes inscribed on its blade are said to ward off all evil that would approach its wielder.
The twin-pronged dagger wielded by a god of thunder and lightning. Its blades generate a boundless supply of electrical energy, unleashing bolts that seem to cover the entire breadth of the sky.
A dagger once carried by a fallen angel. It distorts the fate of its user as it pleases, and domineers heaven and earth as if they were its own possessions.
A dagger made from the claw of a hellfire dragon that even the gods feared. The merciless blasts brought forth from its three claws could render even the highest heavens to ashes.
A pitch-black blade imbued with the power of the dark-winged bird that presides over death. With the power to slay even gods, its merciless strikes serve as a grim summons to the underworld.
A battle glove with a divine aura, modeled after the moon in the night sky. With fists enrobed in moonlight, its wielder can deliver decisive blows that no foe can withstand.
A blood-red pair of clawed gauntlets. Their savage strikes snatch away hope and leave only despair. Death awaits all who face them in battle.
A frosty pair of claws crafted from the ice in the underworld. Those unlucky enough to be struck by these blades will swiftly be frozen, joining the ranks of the dead as an eternal statue of ice.

The gauntlet of a god of mighty storms. Surrounded by a torrent of wind, its blows strike with all the force of miniature tornadoes, and any battlefield where it rages is reduced to a barren wasteland.
A gauntlet said to be made using a shard of a dire wolf's claw. It is feared that in exchange for utilizing its immense power, it will curse any inexperienced wearer and consume their body and mind.
A fist of rock bestowed by Mother Nature upon an indomitable champion to aid in his struggle against tyranny. Imbued with the force of roiling magma, it destroys all creation with a single blow.

A unique gauntlet fabled to be an incarnation of the divine spirit of the plains. In the hands of a true warrior, it boasts greater resilience than the strongest iron, and leads the wielder to martial nirvana.
A bow modeled after a bird with shining metallic wings. Each arrow it fires soars like a bird on the wing and hunts down evil with eagle-eyed precision.
An arcane bow charmed by an ancient queen of demonfolk. The arrows it fires are shrouded in a veil of eerie darkness, and slip through the shadows to silently slay their targets.
A bow bestowed upon a legendary archer by the heavens when his trusty weapon crumbled and his quiver ran dry. Able to withstand the most rapid of volleys, it allows the wielder's true skill to shine.

A gigantic bow once wielded by a mighty hero of legend. Too heavy for ordinary humans to even lift, a single arrow unleashed from its string can pierce the heavens and slay the dragons that rule the sky.
A bow made from the crystallized tears of the Goddess of Winter. The arrows it lets loose are blessed with the goddess's protection, and will permanently freeze any a formidable foe.
A longbow bestowed by Mother Nature upon a hero intent on slaying an evil dragon. Enveloped in the energy of the earth, arrows sent forth from this bow pierce even the heavens' brightest stars.

A hunting bow that houses a spirit of the skies. Firing arrows cloaked in wind that can penetrate any target, it is said to summon entire storms in the hands of a wielder who earns the spirit's approval.
A frigid spear said to have been sealed in a legendary prison of ice. With a single thrust, its target will be frozen alive before they can so much as cry out.
An ancestral greatlance imbued with the grace of a wind deity. Its thrusts are like rapid gusts in a storm, blowing away all that stands in their path.
A holy spear originally wielded by the defenders of a sacred domain. It is said that no menace can be found where its needle edge points, for all evil lies lifeless at its wielder's feet.

The lance of a deity who rules over the underworld. Its crimson point pulsates with the unsuppressable rage of a god condemned to the darkest depths, allowing it to slaughter any foe without restraint.
A legendary spear forged by the Flame Emperor, whose name reached even the heavens. With a tip laced in scorching flames, it can pierce anything as if it were the wrath of the gods themselves.
A heavy spear bestowed by Mother Nature upon a hero who stood up against an evil goddess of calamity. Imbued with the surging power of the earth, with a flash it returns all in this world to dust.
A twin-pronged spear modeled upon the sacred beast that guards a divine realm. Said to hold sway over nature's channels of vitality, its strikes can cause new life to bloom on a parched wasteland.
A scythe-like axe infused with the power of the underworld. Wielded by dark beings who preside over death itself, each baneful swing sends another living soul to the ranks of the departed.
A sacred axe used by the heavens to pass judgment upon mortals. The greater the sin borne by its victims, the more divine power it manifests.
A battleaxe wielded by maiden warriors in ancient times. It is said that the souls it severs from this life are sent to Paradise to meet the gods themselves.

A rugged battleaxe once wielded by a proud, ancient race of titans. Hewn from the rocks of a divine realm, its jagged edges boast incredible mass, allowing them to alter the terrain in a single swing.
An axe equipped with a steam-powered transformation mechanism, a lost technology of an ancient civilization. It is said that when swung at maximum output, it can shatter stars.
A battleaxe tempered in the depths of a mythical ocean. Its superheavy blade, condensed from untold measures of water, summons a torrent of destruction that swallows up all enemies in sight.

A battle-axe housing the spirit of a great flaming bear once revered as the mountain's protector. One who resonates with the spirit can deal scorching blows that bring fortune to their allies and ruin to their foes.
A rod imbued with magical energy from another plane. The sheer power it conceals is overwhelming, but only those with great magical ability of their own can unlock its potential.
A trusty staff that once belonged to the greatest wizard of the era. Said to hold the key to all of creation, one swing is enough to simply erase a monster from existence.
A sacred wand that commands the very thunder that shakes the heavens. Though mere mortals were never meant to wield such power, one with the strength to master it will be undefeatable.

A staff sealing the soul of a dragon that survived a great war of gods. The pitch-black light cast by its lantern engulfs its foes in shadow, consuming their souls, and with each soul it glows ever stronger.
A magic staff that The God of Death stole from the Moon Goddess and threw into the abyss. It eats the fate of its wielder, causing life and death to wax and wane like the moon.

A staff made from the wings of the most beautiful spirit butterfly. Its emerald wings whip up a gust of shimmering scales, depriving foes of their senses and subduing the fiercest beasts without bloodshed.
A cursed staff that imprisons the soul of a legendary serpent king. Conjures a diabolical blaze that binds tenaciously to its victims, refusing to be quelled until it has consumed their very souls.
A rod blessed by a passionate goddess of fire. The light of her love's flames heals not only the wounds of the wielder's allies, but their hearts as well.
A holy rod decorated with a single sacred blossom, crystallized through the power of piety. Producing an endless flow of healing energy, it renders its wielder a veritable goddess.
A rod containing the life energy of the roaring ocean. Its waters wash away all wounds and afflictions, leaving the patient refreshed and ready to face another day.
An arcane rod containing all the wisdom of a master soothsayer. Divining comrades' futures from the movement of the heavens, its orb guides them, focusing the light of the stars into healing energy.
A staff modeled after a branch from Yggdrasil, a tree said to contain various worlds. A single breath of life from its jewel heals all things.
A staff of deep crimson, imbued with the flames of the eternal phoenix. Its overflowing blaze is said to immediately heal the gravest of wounds, and may even bring the dead back to life.
A holy staff blessed by a snake princess of legend. It summons an unceasing flow of holy water that not only heals injuries and illness, but even washes away curses that blight the soul within.
An eerie suit of armor with bewitching effects. All who lay eyes on the purple mist it generates quickly sink into an illusion from which their minds cannot escape.
A form of battle garb created by an ancient race using techniques lost to time. The wearer can soar freely across the battlefield on a pair of invisible wings.

The armor worn by the queen of a bandit tribe that once ruled over an isolated mountain region. Grants the wearer the ferocity of a beast, inspiring wonder and terror alike when set loose on the battlefield.
The armor worn by a mythical tribe of warriors who danced on the battlefield. Though it feels as light as petals fluttering in the wind, it is sturdy enough to withstand the fiercest of assaults.
The rose armor of a legendary warrior princess who herself wielded a sword on the battlefield. The wearer's body will be filled with the spirit of nobility, and will never succumb to fear or despair.

Deep blue armor blessed by the guardian angel of the southern skies. Bestowed upon a hero born to lead the disciples of justice, it is said to grant the benefits of the guardian angel's immense power.
Armor crafted from a clear blue crystal. Harder than any known mineral, it takes a miraculous feat just to carve this crystal, and no process has been found that can stain its gleaming surface.
The armor worn by a valiant maiden who rose up to defend her country in its hour of need. Protected by a mysterious power, it repels all attacks that approach it.
A golden relic recovered from the ruins of a prosperous ancient kingdom. Still retaining its luster from millennia past, this armor's absolute protection will surely never fade.
Heavy armor said to have belonged to a wind deity who dwelled in the rift between heaven and earth. Surrounds the wearer with sharp gusts of wind that repel any who attempt to touch it.

Mirror armor forged by the God of Blacksmiths using silver from the realm of the gods. The polished mirror in the breastplate absorbs and distorts all kinds of magic, then returns it in a tremendous blast of light.
Deep crimson armor blessed by the guardian angel of the northern skies. Forged in the flames of judgment, it is said to grant the benefits of the guardian angel's deep insight and keen perception.
The military uniform worn by a female knight who never knew defeat. Its wearer will surely find a path to victory, no matter how dire the situation may seem.
A set of sacred vestments that can only be worn by an innocent maiden. Its power to repel evil, fueled by the maiden's earnest prayers, know no match.
A set of battle gear imbued with the magic of a terrible flame deity. Its wearer is wreathed in a roaring inferno, quickly incinerating any threats that may draw near.
The battle garb of spies in service to the king of the underworld. Draws out the wearer's full potential for covert lethality, allowing them to leave their mark in the hidden annals of history.
A dress worn by a legendary dancer. Upon donning the outfit, the wearer's body takes on the properties of water, which allows them to flounder enemies in ever-changing, current-like movements.
A deep green dress blessed by the guardian angel of the eastern skies. Imbued with healing winds that keep illness at bay, it is said to grant the benefits of the guardian angel's love and devotion.
The robes worn by a holy maiden who has devoted her life to the gods. They grant the wearer the grace of the divine, preventing all harm that might befall them from evil powers.
A fine robe once worn by a mighty empress. Each individual thread is imbued with the empress's own magic, allowing it to repel all outside magical interference.
The robe of the so-called Wizard King, a legendary figure said to have mastered many thousands of spells. Those wearers it deems worthy gain access to its original owner's fount of knowledge.
A mystical robe said to have once been worn by a line of female hermits who ruled over an icy realm. Slip your arms through its sleeves, and its aura will nullify all impacts that assault you.

The robe of a prophet with the power to divine anything and everything by reading the stars. Simply by wearing it, one can foresee all sorts of disasters, and decipher anything by observing the orbits of the planets.

Moon-white vestments blessed by the guardian angel of the western skies. Illuminating a path through this chaotic world, it is said to grant the benefits of the guardian angel's all-encompassing fortune.
A round shield engraved with a chart of the heavens. Itself imbued with celestial energies, it guides all attacks away from its wielder, leaving their safety written in the stars.
A mirror shield forged from silver from the realm of the gods combined with thousands of magic spells. Its mirrored surface neither scratches nor fogs, and even reflects curses.

It is said that a warrior princess wore these greaves until the day she fell in battle, just short of completing her great conquest.\nHer bitter regret lingers in them still as a powerful magical force.
A pair of winged golden shoes, crafted from angel feathers. Though they require extensive training to use effectively, once mastered, they allow the wearer to leap freely through the sky.
War boots blessed by the guardian angels of the skies. Adorned with feathers from all four cardinal angels, their unparalleled sacred aura repels all curses and every kind of suffering.
The shoes worn by an infamous witch who led nations to ruin with her otherworldly beauty and hedonistic character. Simply wearing them summons illusions that drive one's foes to madness.

Leg armor forged from silver from the realm of the gods combined with the essence of alchemy. With each step, it produces a lifelike reflection of the wearer, amassing to an inexhaustible army to intimidate foes.
The dashing headwear worn by a legendary Captain of the Guard. The large decorative feather inspires valiance in not only the wearer, but all who witness its majestic plumes.
The crown worn by the queen of a land long since fallen and forgotten. Those who wear it are blessed with great magical energy, but also find themselves filled with an unexplainable sadness.
Ceremonial headwear granted to holy women who have earned great respect from the populace. When worn by the pure of heart, it repels those with untoward intentions.

A veil carrying the blessing of its former owner, a holy woman who sacrificed herself for the good of humanity. It is said that those who possess it can discern all fortune and calamity that lies ahead.
Hallowed headwear blessed by the guardian angels of the earth. Bestowed only upon true seekers of the light, it is said that those who wear it can reach the realm of heavenly miracles.
A pair of earrings bearing magical crystals mined from a thousand-year-old stratum. The vast natural energies they have absorbed over the years provide a powerful magical protection to the wearer.
A mystical pendant said to contain the sealed rage of a dragon. As an incarnation of fury itself, it grants the wearer the strength to shake mountains and sunder the earth.

A bracelet containing a war deity's tempestuous soul. By drawing on magical energy in the atmosphere, it grants its bearer the strength to crush mountains, but only a well-trained fighter can control it.
An ornamental hairpin worn by a legendary female ninja who lived through an era of intrigue and betrayal. Enchanted with a spell that grants demonic strength to even the daintiest of bodies.

A ring-shaped concealed weapon favored by a legendary assassin from the dark world. With the flames of hell residing in its thorn, crafted to resemble a fire dragon's claw, a single prick burns even bone down to nothing.

A neck adornment in the shape of a crimson rose, said to be favored by the Goddess of War. It resonates with the wearer's warrior spirit, and with a scarlet radiance brings forth the goddess' protection.
A pair of earrings blessed by the king of spirits. With protective power vast enough to cover an entire forest, it rejects any and all calamities that might befall the wearer.
A pendant made from the crystallized tears of a mermaid princess. Her endless love shines more brilliantly than the finest sapphire, purifying all curses that afflict the wearer.

The bracelet of a great monarch known for defending his realm from countless threats. It draws magic from its surroundings to form a sturdy barrier, allowing its wielder to be a shield to their allies.
A hair ornament formed from the scales of a divine beast who rules the seven seas. Those who wear it are granted the ocean's blessing, rendering them as impervious to attack as the mighty waves.

A ring blessed with the protection of the shield goddess. Placing it upon a finger deploys an immense magical shield that spans thousands of miles, protecting the wearer from all pain, evil, and misfortune that may come their way.
A necklace with the magically recreated wings of a spirit butterfly said to only inhabit Paradise. A flap of its wings distorts causality, silently halting even a fatal blow.
A pair of earrings modeled after the trident said to be wielded by the ruler of the sea. The crystal at its center, bluer than the ocean depths, confers enough magic to calm the stormy waves.
A necklace imbued with the blessings of that purest of sacred beasts, the unicorn. The holy light in its horn amplifies the wearer's own magical energy, allowing them to perform miraculous feats.

A relic left by a great sage who attained divinity through wisdom alone. Draws magical energy to the wearer in torrents, but only if they have sufficient clarity of mind. Otherwise, it rejects them entirely.

An ornate ribbon adorned with the single tear shed by an icy-hearted princess when she first learned to love. Preserved as an unmelting droplet of ice, it grants the ability to command mighty blizzards.

Excavated from ancient rock deep within the earth, this ring is adorned with a crystal that contains immense magical power. It amplifies magic hundreds of times, but due to the difficulty using it, only outstanding practitioners can wield it.
Magical equipment said to have been bestowed upon humanity by a chaos deity. The elaborate magic circle inscribed within its gem draws an inexhaustible amount of magical power from another world.
